<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1156,1078,1728]" lastBlockId="10.[160,1156,142,549]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="321" pageId="9" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,268,1078,1104]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="320">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="De Man JG" box="[285,450,1079,1104]" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" pagination="3 - 62" refId="ref18320" refString="De Man JG. 1921. Nouvelles recherches sur les nematode libres terricoles de la Holland. Cap Zoologica. 1: 3 - 62." type="journal article" year="1921">De Man (1921)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Man" authorityYear="1921" box="[574,825,1079,1104]" class="Adenophorea" family="Dorylaimidae" genus="Dorylaimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="micoletzkyi">
<emphasis box="[574,825,1079,1104]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="320">Dorylaimus micoletzkyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[894,1078,1079,1104]" name="Netherlands" pageId="9" pageNumber="320">the Netherlands</collectingCountry>
, which was later transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorne and Swanger" authorityYear="1936" box="[425,580,1114,1139]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[425,580,1114,1139]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="320">Dorylaimoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Thorne G &amp; Swanger HH" box="[621,930,1114,1139]" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" pagination="223" refId="ref19695" refString="Thorne G, Swanger HH. 1936. A monograph of the nematode genera Dorylaimus Dujardin, Aporcelaimus n. g., Dorylaimoides n. g., and Pungentus n. g. Cap Zoologica. 6: 223." type="journal article" year="1936">Thorne and Swanger (1936)</bibRefCitation>
in their monograph when they proposed the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorne and Swanger" authorityYear="1936" box="[538,693,1149,1174]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[538,693,1149,1174]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="320">Dorylaimoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Thorne G" box="[710,870,1149,1174]" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref19654" refString="Thorne G. 1974. Nematodes of the Northern Great plains. Part II. Dorylaimoidea in part (Nemata: Adenophorea). Tech Bull Agric Exp Station, South Dakota State Univ. 41: 1 - 20." type="journal article" year="1974">Thorne (1974)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed this species from the 
<collectingCountry box="[262,312,1183,1208]" name="United States of America" pageId="9" pageNumber="320">USA</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Goseco CG &amp; Ferris VR &amp; Ferris JM" box="[320,536,1183,1208]" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" refId="ref18466" refString="Goseco CG, Ferris VR, Ferris JM. 1976. Revision in Leptonchoidea (Nematoda: Dorylaimida). Dorylaimoides in Dorylaimoididae, Dorylaimoididinae, Calolaimus and Timmus n. gen. in Dorylaimoididae, Calolaiminae, and Miranema in Mirannematidae. Res. Bull., Agric. Expt. Sta., Purdue Univ., West Lafayette No. 941; p. 46." type="journal volume" year="1976">Goseco et al. (1976)</bibRefCitation>
made a detailed study of this species based on the 
<typeStatus box="[1105,1155,1183,1208]" pageId="9" pageNumber="320">type</typeStatus>
population as well as specimens from several localities in the 
<collectingCountry box="[840,890,1218,1243]" name="United States of America" pageId="9" pageNumber="320">USA</collectingCountry>
. They also synonymised 
<taxonomicName authority="Siddiqi, 1964" authorityName="Siddiqi" authorityYear="1964" box="[160,620,1253,1278]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="pakistanensis">
<emphasis box="[160,468,1253,1278]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="320">Dorylaimoides pakistanensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Siddiqi MR" box="[475,620,1253,1278]" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" pagination="626 - 634" refId="ref19460" refString="Siddiqi MR. 1964. Three new species of Dorylaimoides Thorne &amp; Swanger, 1936, with descriptions of Xiphinema orbum n. sp. (Nematoda: Dorylaimoidea). Nematologica. 9 (4): 626 - 634. doi: 10.1163 / 187529263 X 00737." type="journal article" year="1964">Siddiqi, 1964</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
with this species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorne and Swanger" authorityYear="1936" baseAuthorityName="de Man" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[826,1109,1253,1278]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="micoletzkyi">
<emphasis box="[826,1109,1253,1278]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="320">Dorylaimoides micoletzkyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a wide distribution and has been redescribed from 
<collectingCountry box="[727,782,1287,1312]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="320">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ahmad M &amp; Jairajpuri MS" box="[794,1094,1287,1312]" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" pagination="125 - 135" refId="ref17871" refString="Ahmad M, Jairajpuri MS. 1979. Four new species of Leptonchidae (Nematoda: Dorylaimida). Ind J Nematol. 9: 125 - 135." type="journal article" year="1979">Ahmad and Jairajpuri 1979</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Jana A &amp; Baqri QH" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref18975" refString="Jana A, Baqri QH. 1981. Nematodes from West Bengal (India) XI. Studies on the species of the superfamily Leptonchoidea (Dorylaimida). J Zoo Soc Ind. 33: 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1981">Jana and Baqri 1981</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Baqri QH" box="[376,508,1322,1347]" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" pagination="1 - 103" refId="ref18088" refString="Baqri QH. 1991. Contribution to the fauna of Sikkim. Nematodes associated with citrus from Sikkim, India. Records of the zoological survey of India. Occas Pap. 128: 1 - 103." type="journal article" year="1991">Baqri 1991</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[540,638,1322,1347]" name="Hungary" pageId="9" pageNumber="320">Hungary</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Andrassy I" box="[661,840,1322,1347]" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" pagination="129 - 197" refId="ref18046" refString="Andrassy I. 1991. The free-living nematodes fauna of the Batorliget nature reserve, and Mahunka S, editor. The Batorliget nature reserve after forty years. Hungarian Natural History Museum, Budapest; p. 129 - 197." type="book chapter" year="1991">Andrássy 1991</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[926,990,1322,1347]" name="Spain" pageId="9" pageNumber="320">Spain</collectingCountry>
(Peralta and Peña-Santiago 1995). The morphometrics of the present population conforms well with the 
<typeStatus box="[207,257,1391,1416]" pageId="9" pageNumber="320">type</typeStatus>
population except in having a shorter body (L = 1.0–1.1 vs 
<quantity box="[961,1095,1391,1416]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2999999999999998" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" unit="mm" value="1.2999999999999998" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.4 mm</quantity>
) and slightly lower c ratio (18.1–18.8 vs 19–26). It also conforms well with the 
<collectingCountry box="[968,1015,1426,1451]" name="United States of America" pageId="9" pageNumber="320">USA</collectingCountry>
populations described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Thorne G" box="[309,465,1461,1486]" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref19654" refString="Thorne G. 1974. Nematodes of the Northern Great plains. Part II. Dorylaimoidea in part (Nemata: Adenophorea). Tech Bull Agric Exp Station, South Dakota State Univ. 41: 1 - 20." type="journal article" year="1974">Thorne (1974)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Goseco CG &amp; Ferris VR &amp; Ferris JM" box="[519,737,1461,1486]" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" refId="ref18466" refString="Goseco CG, Ferris VR, Ferris JM. 1976. Revision in Leptonchoidea (Nematoda: Dorylaimida). Dorylaimoides in Dorylaimoididae, Dorylaimoididinae, Calolaimus and Timmus n. gen. in Dorylaimoididae, Calolaiminae, and Miranema in Mirannematidae. Res. Bull., Agric. Expt. Sta., Purdue Univ., West Lafayette No. 941; p. 46." type="journal volume" year="1976">Goseco et al. (1976)</bibRefCitation>
. The present specimens conform well with all the Indian populations except for differing from 
<bibRefCitation author="Ahmad M &amp; Jairajpuri MS" box="[815,1156,1495,1520]" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" pagination="125 - 135" refId="ref17871" refString="Ahmad M, Jairajpuri MS. 1979. Four new species of Leptonchidae (Nematoda: Dorylaimida). Ind J Nematol. 9: 125 - 135." type="journal article" year="1979">Ahmad and Jairajpuri’s (1979)</bibRefCitation>
population in having a slightly less slender body (a = 32–36 vs 38–41) and a lower c ratio (18 vs 20–22); from 
<bibRefCitation author="Jana A &amp; Baqri QH" box="[386,647,1565,1590]" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref18975" refString="Jana A, Baqri QH. 1981. Nematodes from West Bengal (India) XI. Studies on the species of the superfamily Leptonchoidea (Dorylaimida). J Zoo Soc Ind. 33: 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1981">Jana and Baqri’s (1981)</bibRefCitation>
population in having a slightly shorter body (L = 1.0–1.1 vs 
<quantity box="[325,458,1599,1624]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.3 mm</quantity>
), lower c ratio (18 vs 21–23), slightly smaller spicules (29–32 vs 36 μm) and more ventromedian supplements (7–8 vs 5); and from 
<bibRefCitation author="Baqri QH" box="[910,1061,1634,1659]" pageId="9" pageNumber="320" pagination="1 - 103" refId="ref18088" refString="Baqri QH. 1991. Contribution to the fauna of Sikkim. Nematodes associated with citrus from Sikkim, India. Records of the zoological survey of India. Occas Pap. 128: 1 - 103." type="journal article" year="1991">Baqri’s (1991)</bibRefCitation>
population in having an anterior vulva position (V = 40–41 vs 44–46), lower c’ ratio (2.8–2.9 vs 3.5–4.0), smaller spicules (29–32 vs 36 μm) and more ventromedian supplements (7.0–8.0 vs 5.0). The present population also conforms well with the Hungarian population except in having a slightly shorter body (L = 1.0–1.1 vs 
<quantity box="[690,823,177,202]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="10" pageNumber="321" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.1">1.1–1.4 mm</quantity>
), and differs from the Spanish population in having a slightly less slender body (a = 32–36 vs 37–45).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,1156,142,549]" pageId="10" pageNumber="321">
The present population conforms well with all the earlier described populations, except for differing from the 
<collectingCountry box="[496,589,281,306]" name="Pakistan" pageId="10" pageNumber="321">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
population described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Siddiqi MR" box="[884,1040,281,306]" pageId="10" pageNumber="321" pagination="626 - 634" refId="ref19460" refString="Siddiqi MR. 1964. Three new species of Dorylaimoides Thorne &amp; Swanger, 1936, with descriptions of Xiphinema orbum n. sp. (Nematoda: Dorylaimoidea). Nematologica. 9 (4): 626 - 634. doi: 10.1163 / 187529263 X 00737." type="journal article" year="1964">Siddiqi (1964)</bibRefCitation>
in having a slightly less slender body (a = 32–36 vs 36–46); shorter tail (56–59 vs 80); higher c (18.1– 18.8 vs 12.5–16) and lower c’ (2.8–2.9 vs 4.5) ratios and more ventromedian supplements (7–8 vs 5–6). Peña-Santiago and Peralta (1997) did not consider the 
<bibRefCitation author="Siddiqi MR" box="[993,1155,385,410]" pageId="10" pageNumber="321" pagination="626 - 634" refId="ref19460" refString="Siddiqi MR. 1964. Three new species of Dorylaimoides Thorne &amp; Swanger, 1936, with descriptions of Xiphinema orbum n. sp. (Nematoda: Dorylaimoidea). Nematologica. 9 (4): 626 - 634. doi: 10.1163 / 187529263 X 00737." type="journal article" year="1964">Siddiqi (1964)</bibRefCitation>
population similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorne and Swanger" authorityYear="1936" baseAuthorityName="de Man" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[410,563,420,445]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="10" pageNumber="321" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="micoletzkyi">
<emphasis box="[410,563,420,445]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="321">D. micoletzkyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the presence of a longer tail (84 vs 48–80) lower c ratio (12.5–16 vs 16–29) and shorter spicules (29–30 vs 32–38). These differences are also distinct in the present specimens; hence we agree with Peña-Santiago and Peralta (1997) and do not consider the 
<collectingCountry box="[518,611,524,549]" name="Pakistan" pageId="10" pageNumber="321">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
population conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorne and Swanger" authorityYear="1936" baseAuthorityName="de Man" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[938,1088,524,549]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="10" pageNumber="321" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="micoletzkyi">
<emphasis box="[938,1088,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="321">D. micoletzkyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
